                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Myself, I like to use mark npc to let the group know which mobs to take out next.
<br />

<br />
We pull a few mobs... group goes after one of them, I mez the rest.  Then, I tash, slow, and blur (having clicky slow and blur helps), and when I blur a mob, I mark it, so the tank knows they can just attack it without worrying about agro.
<br />

<br />
I just wish there was a way to target the marked npc's from the command line, so my tanks could hotkey it.  Even still, its handy.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=378985" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Tashim</a>
