                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I really was impressed the first time i saw a colored ring around my group members. I remember it being a thrilling enhancement for my targeting abilities. It led to further mastery of CC and buffing groups in rapid pull and kill ldon adventures. The improvement led my groups to getting finished in 30 minute level 65 adventures and we would wait around complaining about waiting the 15 minutes to start another one, still pulsing from the rush. 
<br />

<br />
Raiding in COD after finishing Grummus and CODa the previous day was so exhausting but I was on my game again and loving the exertion. One thing that made Raids so much easier was Mark NPC. The Main Raid Tank running around with big white glowing rings around while a  full raid of 72 players smashed into each other like a massive school of pirranha. The HOTT window led our group into comfort knowing our Main Tank was still standing and gave us an up to date on our current mob health without a word spoken, we all swarmed in silent tempest.
<br />

<br />
The health enhancement at level 3 is 100 more hitpoints for the group and the others are nice to have, but one stands out more than any, HOTT. Mark NPC is another one for raids since it can be used to mark the raid Main Tank as the raid moves from place to place.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><img src="images/smiles/eusa_drool.gif" alt="eusa_drool.gif" border="0" /> <span style="color: violet"></span></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Chicks Rule, Boys Drool <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /></td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
